alembic init [directory]
Intialize a new Alembic enviornment in the specified directory.
This sets up the configuration files and scripts directory needed for migrations.

alembic revision -m "message" [--autogenerate]
Create a new migration script.
   use -m to add a message describing the migration
   Add --autogenerate to automatically generate migration code based on model and database differences. 

alembic upgrade [revision]
Apply migrations up to the specified revision (e.g.,head for the latest).This updates  the database schema to desired
state.

alembic upgrade +2
This command    upgrades you database  schema forward by two migrations steps from the current revision, applying  the next two migrations sequence.

alembic downgrade [revision]
Revert migrations down to the specified revision, effectively rolling back the schema changes.

alembic downgrade -1 
This command downgrades (rolls back) your database schema by one migration step from the current revision , reverting the most recent migration

alembic current
Display the current revisions applied  to the database.

alembic history
Show the list of all migration scripts in chronological order

alembic check
check if there are pending upgrade operations when using autogenerate .